it.uniud.mads.jlibbig.core.attachedProperties

Class PropertyContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.uniud.mads.jlibbig.core.attachedProperties.PropertyContainer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PropertyTarget

    public class PropertyContainer
extends java.lang.Object
implements PropertyTarget
    The class provides a default implementation of the PropertyTarget interface. This class must be used to handle properties by classes implementing the interface in order to make properties aware of the objects to which are attached (see Property.onAttach(it.uniud.mads.jlibbig.core.attachedProperties.PropertyTarget) and Property.onDetach(it.uniud.mads.jlibbig.core.attachedProperties.PropertyTarget)). The container requires a reference to the object to which the properties are attached in order to enact it; if no reference is provided, the container will use a reference to itself.
